## What I built

A server-rendered **Express + SQLite** clinic portal with real role-based access control. SQLite uses Node's **built-in `node:sqlite`** (your Node v24.16 supports it), so `npm install` is **pure JS ‚Äî no native compilation** on Windows.

```
package.json          deps: express, express-session, ejs, bcryptjs
README.md             how to run on port 5092 + demo accounts
src/
  server.js           app wiring, sessions, role-based home redirect (port 5092)
  db.js               SQLite connection + schema (users, appointments, medical_records)
  seed.js             idempotent demo data  (npm run seed)
  middleware.js       requireLogin / requireRole
  routes/auth.js      login/logout, bcrypt password check
  routes/patient.js   book + view/cancel OWN appointments & records
  routes/doctor.js    own schedule + own patients' records (view/add)
  routes/reception.js clinic-wide schedule (confirm/cancel/reschedule)
views/  public/style.css
```

## How access is enforced (the core requirement)

Two layers on every request:
1. **Role gate** ‚Äî each role's router starts with `requireRole('patient'|'doctor'|'receptionist')`; wrong role ‚Üí **403**.
2. **Ownership scoping** ‚Äî every query is filtered to the logged-in user, so IDs can't be guessed:
   - Patient: `WHERE patient_id = <me>` for records/appointments; cancel only own.
   - Doctor: a patient is only "theirs" if they share an appointment (`isMyPatient`); records are stamped with the doctor's own id server-side.
   - Receptionist: manages the schedule but **has no medical-records route at all** (clinical confidentiality).

